 Chat Application

A simple Java console application designed for secure user registration and login.

 Features
Registration:Validates username, password, and phone number formats.
Login: Authenticates users by checking entered credentials against stored data.
Testing: Includes JUnit tests to ensure all validation logic works correctly.

Validation Rules
Username: Maximum 5 characters and must include an underscore ("_").
Password: Minimum 8 characters, including uppercase, lowercase, a digit, and a special character.
Phone:Accepts 10 digits (`1234567890`) or dashed format (`123-456-7890`).

 Project Structure
ChatApplication.java: The main entry point for the console UI.
LoginAuthenticator.java: Handles the logic for verifying login attempts.
UserRegistration.java: Manages user data and calls the validator.
RegistrationValidator.java: Contains the specific logic (RegEx) for data requirements.
test Packages: Contains "LoginAuthenticatorTest" and "RegistrationValidatorTest" for quality assurance.

Setup
1. Open the project in NetBeans.
2. Ensure "JUnit 4.13.2" is added to your library path.
3. Run `ChatApplication.java` to start the program.
4. To run tests, right-click the project and select Test.

 Technologies
Java SDK 25
JUnit 4 (Testing)
NetBeans IDE
